review_blob:
Pours with bubbly white head
Strong yeast aroma with slight hoppy citrus
Bubbly mouth feel
Slight alcohol flavor followed by a sweet bitterness
Mmmmm...

Perfect balance of flavor
Bitterness is noticeable, but not overwhelming
Hop flavor is there, but does not have the polarizing effect of an ipa
beer_name: Deschutes Red Chair Northwest Pale Ale

review_blob:
This fresh hopped beast anything but sucks. Opens with an excellent fresh hopped aroma and delivers on the fresh hop promise with a beautiful earthy taste and an almost orange peel after taste.

The smoothness and slight maltyness enhance the profile making the perfect American ipa.

Hats off!

Smooth. Bitter.

Strong grapefruit after taste. Very dry finish. Another one and done. Too rich for drinking all night.
Very clear. Smooth mouth feel. Bitter hit of hops as it bubbles in your mouth. Strong bitter after taste. Relatively mild and smooth, but the bitter after taste means one and done on this guy.

Cask - hopped with mosaic- thick black appearance. Light frothy head. Aroma of camel and coffee. Taste very powerful. earthy hop notes followed by caramel and finish with a dry bitter feel.

Mmmmmm...
beer_name: Indeed Midnight Ryder American Black Ale

review_blob:

Well balanced with the hops

Not a very strong aroma

Mouth feel like a pale ale
After feel bitterness of one
But the grape fruit/ apricot mixed with the caramel and smoky undertones make me think porter or stout
Something very different
I like it

Stout
Chocolate and coffee tones
Some moderate bitterness which adds to the flavor
Not the most inventive of all the beers at steel toe

Go for a Douglas or a provider!

Can you say hops?

Great earthy taste. Very bitter, mouthfeel is very smooth, but perfectly carbonated.

Great hoppy flavor
Very fresh tasting 
Tap is the best, but a can will always do.

Strong floral aroma with a crisp, dry mouth feel. Hoppy taste, period. Tangy after taste.

One of the best high hop american IPAs out there.
Creamy, malty texture. Rich, flavorful head. Sweet, slightly bitter flavor. Lighter in flavor than some traditional Oktoberfest beers. Incredibly tasty. A perfect fall beer.
Tasting with a lemon. Really complement s flavor. Nice yeasty floral flavor. Good carbonation, not sparkly, but bubbly.
Great lager. Light feel, but lots of flavor. Reminds me of Grain belt premium, but darker with a more caramel taste.
